TableContextTimeStampAfterTable: {49633=The Decemberists – Down By The Water – from the forthcoming LP “The King Is Dead” (Capitol, 2010) R.E.M. – The One I Love (live) – Document (I.R.S., 1987) Elliott Smith – Waltz #2 – An Introduction To Elliott Smith (Kill Rock Stars, 2010) **REQUEST Syd Barrett – Octopus (2010 Mix) – An Introduction To Syd Barrett (EMI, 2010) Lee Hazlewood with Nancy Sinatra – Some Velvet Morning – Movin’ With Nancy (Reprise, 1968), 110975=1973 Hathor (liturgie du souffle pour la resurerection des morts), 111167=1979 Let's Start, 131361=Copyright © 2012 KBOO Community Radio | Copyright Policy | Community Guidelines | Website Illustration & Design by: KMF ILLUSTRATION, 111063=1975 Les Fous d'Or, 102489=Annual Gales of November Show: Songs about shipwrecks, lighthouses, mermaids, and general nautical mayhem- inspired by Gordon Lightfoots' classic "Wreck of the Edmund Fitgerald", 122938=Latest newsletter: May 2015, 109919=Tonight we listen to the music of Igor Wakhevitch.  On top of composing music for Salvador Dali's 1974 opera "Etre Dieu," Wakhevitch released six records in the 1970s. The Swan's Michael Gira said of Wakhevitch "The most astonishing music I have heard in some years... Ominous and beautiful, then clamorous and Wagnerian," while a Pitchfork review of one Wakhevitch's records, "Docteur Faust," was titled "It Was the Strangest Record I Had Ever Heard."  While sections of the Dali Opera have been and will be aired on Desolo Vox Luna Theatrum, I thought it'd be nice to hear from those 6 albums released in the 1970s. These albums were also reissued several years ago as the 6-CD set "Donc" by the Fractal label. , 111104=1977 Nagual (les ailes de la perception), 118802=November 15th, America Recycles Day and recyled tunes are featured on the Noontime Jamboree.}
